      "message": "$CTS/cts/tests/tests/hardware/src/android/hardware/cts/helpers/sensorverification/EventTimestampSynchronizationVerification.java\n\nThis is the file that checks the event timestamps. In the function verifyTimestampSynchronization():\n\nlong eventTimestampNs \u003d event.timestamp;\nlong receivedTimestampNs \u003d event.receivedTimestamp;\nlong upperThresholdNs \u003d receivedTimestampNs;\nlong lowerThresholdNs \u003d receivedTimestampNs - mMaximumSynchronizationErrorNs\n                    - mExpectedSyncLatencyNs;\nif (eventTimestampNs \u003c lowerThresholdNs || eventTimestampNs \u003e upperThresholdNs) { ... }\n\nas you can see, event\u0027s |received_timestamp| is the _upper_ threshold for the |timestamp| field we set in it\n\n|received_timestamp| is just the guest\u0027s timestamp at the moment of event arrival\n|timestamp| is what emulator sends with a \"sync:%ts%\" message",
